<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,248,1431,1455]" pageId="26" pageNumber="300">Remark</emphasis>
: Although this species is commonly found active at dusk and early night, 
<specimenCount box="[1034,1155,1431,1455]" pageId="26" pageNumber="300" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
was found on one occasion feeding on a 
<taxonomicName box="[604,732,1465,1490]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lucidota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[604,694,1465,1490]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="300">Lucidota</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
during daytime, shortly after noon.
</paragraph>
